ocean_sigma_z.z_factors: sigma: sigma eta: eta depth: depth depth_c: depth_c nsigma: nsigma zlev: zlev
ocean_sigma_z.z_bounds_factors: sigma: sigma_bnds eta: eta depth: depth depth_c: depth_c nsigma: nsigma zlev: zlev_bnds
ocean_sigma_z.formula: for k <= nsigma: z(n,k,j,i) = eta(n,j,i) + sigma(k)*(min(depth_c,depth(j,i))+eta(n,j,i)) ; for k > nsigma: z(n,k,j,i) = zlev(k)

smooth_level.z_factors: a: a b1: b1 b2: b2 ztop: ztop zsurf1: zsurf1 zsurf2: zsurf2
smooth_level.z_bounds_factors: a: a_bnds b1: b1_bnds b2: b2_bnds ztop: ztop zsurf1: zsurf1 zsurf2: zsurf2

ocean_sigma.z_factors: sigma: lev eta: eta depth: depth
ocean_sigma.z_bounds_factors: sigma: lev_bnds eta: eta depth: depth

ocean_s.z_factors: s: lev eta: eta depth: depth a: a_coeff b: b_coeff depth_c: depth_c
ocean_s.z_bounds_factors: s: lev_bnds eta: eta depth: depth a: a b: b depth_c: depth_c
ocean_s.formula: z(n,k,j,i) = eta(n,j,i)*(1+s(k)) + depth_c*s(k) + (depth(j,i)-depth_c)*C(k) n where n C(k)=(1-b)*sinh(a*s(k))/sinh(a) +n           b*(tanh(a*(s(k)+0.5))/(2*tanh(0.5*a)) - 0.5)

alternate_hybrid_sigma.z_factors: ap: ap b: b ps: ps
alternate_hybrid_sigma.z_bounds_factors: ap: ap_bnds b: b_bnds ps: ps

time3.long_name: Diurnal cycle: monthly mean of the diurnal cycle (1 hour steps).

dbze.long_name: CloudSat simulator equivalent radar reflectivity factor

standard_sigma.z_factors: ptop: ptop sigma: lev ps: ps
standard_sigma.z_bounds_factors: ptop: ptop sigma: lev_bnds ps: ps

hybrid_height.z_factors: a: lev b: b orog: orog
hybrid_height.z_bounds_factors: a: lev_bnds b: b_bnds orog: orog

ocean_double_sigma.z_factors: sigma: sigma depth: depth z1: z1 z2: z2 a: a_coeff href: href k_c: k_c
ocean_double_sigma.z_bounds_factors: sigma: sigma_bnds depth: depth z1: z1 z2: z2 a: a href: href k_c: k_c
ocean_double_sigma.formula: for k <= k_c:n z(k,j,i)= sigma(k)*f(j,i) n for k > k_c:n z(k,j,i)= f(j,i) + (sigma(k)-1)*(depth(j,i)-f(j,i)) n f(j,i)= 0.5*(z1+ z2) + 0.5*(z1-z2)* tanh(2*a/(z1-z2)*(depth(j,i)-href))

standard_hybrid_sigma.z_factors: p0: p0 a: a b: b ps: ps
standard_hybrid_sigma.z_bounds_factors: p0: p0 a: a_bnds b: b_bnds ps: ps

wvelbase.long_name: Z-component of land ice basal velocity
wvelbase.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

litausb.comment: The magnitude of the shear stress at land ice base
litausb.long_name: Magnitude of land ice basal shear stress
litausb.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

cSoil.comment: Carbon mass in the full depth of the soil model.
cSoil.long_name: Carbon Mass in Model Soil Pool

sftgrf.comment: Fraction of grid cell covered by grounded ice sheet
sftgrf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where grounded_ice_sheet

uvelmean.comment: The vertical mean land ice velocity is the average from the bedrock to the surface of the ice
uvelmean.long_name: X-component of land ice vertical mean velocity
uvelmean.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

litaulb.comment: The magnitude of the longitudinal stress at land ice base
litaulb.long_name: Magnitude of land ice basal longitudinal stress
litaulb.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

orog.comment: The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere. Altitude is the (geometric) height above the geoid, which is the reference geopotential surface. The geoid is similar to mean sea level.
orog.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

iareagl.comment: Total area of the grounded ice in Greenland
iareagl.long_name: Area covered by grounded ice sheet
iareagl.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where grounded_ice_sheet

uvelbase.long_name: X-component of land ice basal velocity
uvelbase.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

osaltrmadvect.long_name: Tendency of Sea Water Salinity Expressed as Salt Content due to Residual Mean Advection

ocontemppadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized eddy advection (any form of eddy advection). Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.
ocontemppadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized eddy advection

wvelsurf.long_name: Z-component of land ice surface velocity
wvelsurf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

sftflf.comment: Fraction of grid cell covered by ice sheet flowing over seawater
sftflf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where floating_ice_sheet

hfgeoubed.long_name: Geothermal Heat flux beneath land ice
hfgeoubed.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

cVeg.comment: Carbon mass per unit area in vegetation.

cSoilLut.comment: end of year values (not annual mean)
cSoilLut.long_name: Carbon in Soil Pool on Landuse Tiles

uvelsurf.long_name: X-component of land ice surface velocity
uvelsurf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

tnkebto.comment: Depth integrated impacts on kinetic energy arising from parameterized eddy-induced advection. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was 3d, whereas the CMIP6 depth integrated diagnostic is sufficient for many purposes and reduces archive requirements.
tnkebto.long_name: tendency of ocean eddy kinetic energy content due to parameterized eddy advection

cAnt.comment: grid cell mean carbon in anthropogenic pools into which harvests and cleared carbon are deposited before release into atmosphere PLUS any remaining anthropogenic pools that may be associated with lands which were converted into land use tiles during reported period . Does NOT include residue which is deposited into soil or litter; end of year values (not annual mean)

vvelsurf.long_name: Y-component of land ice surface velocity
vvelsurf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

ocontemprmadvect.long_name: Tendency of Sea Water Conservative Temperature Expressed as Heat Content due to Residual Mean Advection

limass.comment: Computed as the volume times density
limass.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

fracLut.comment: end of year values (not annual mean); note that fraction should be reported as fraction of atmospheric grid cell (example: frac_lnd = 0.5, frac_ocn = 0.5, frac_crop_lnd = 0.2 (of land portion of grid cell), then frac_lut(crp) = 0.5*0.2 = 0.1)
fracLut.long_name: fraction of grid cell for each land use tile

acabf.comment: Specific mass balance of land ice (the net rate at which ice is added per unit area at the land ice surface; computed as the total surface mass balance on the land ice portion of the grid cell divided by land ice area in the grid cell). A negative value means loss of ice.
acabf.long_name: Land Ice Surface Mass Balance flux
acabf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

snc.comment: Fraction of each grid cell that is occupied by snow that rests on land portion of cell.
snc.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

opottemprmadvect.long_name: Tendency of Sea Eater Potential Temperature Expressed as Heat Content due to Residual Mean Advection

cVegLut.comment: end of year values (not annual mean)
cVegLut.long_name: carbon in vegetation on land use tiles

vvelmean.comment: The vertical mean land ice velocity is the average from the bedrock to the surface of the ice
vvelmean.long_name: Y-component of land ice vertical mean velocity
vvelmean.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

cAntLut.comment: anthropogenic pools associated with land use tiles into which harvests and cleared carbon are deposited before release into atmosphere PLUS any remaining anthropogenic pools that may be associated with lands which were converted into land use tiles during reported period . Does NOT include residue which is deposited into soil or litter; end of year values (not annual mean)
cAntLut.long_name: Carbon in Anthropogenic Pools Associated with Landuse Tiles

litaunb.comment: The magnitude of the normal stress at land ice base
litaunb.long_name: Magnitude of land ice basal normal stress
litaunb.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

topg.comment: The bedrock topography beneath the land ice
topg.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

fracInLut.comment: cumulative fractional transitions over the year; note that fraction should be reported as fraction of atmospheric grid cell
fracInLut.long_name: annual gross fraction that was transferred into this tile from other land use tiles

litempsnic.comment: Surface Temperature that is used to force ice sheet models. It does not vary with seasons. In some models it is the temperature at the base of the snow, and in other at the base of firn. Report surface temperature of ice sheet where snow or firn thickness is zero
litempsnic.long_name: Temperature at the interface between land ice and snow or firn
litempsnic.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

iareafl.comment: Total area of the floating ice shelves of Greenland
iareafl.long_name: Area covered by floating ice shelves
iareafl.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where floating_ice_sheet

p0.long_name: vertical coordinate formula term: reference pressure

licalvf.comment: Loss of ice mass resulting from iceberg calving. Computed as the rate of mass loss by the ice shelf (in kg s-1) divided by the horizontal area of the ice sheet (m2) in the grid box.
licalvf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

zfull.long_name: Depth Below Geoid of Ocean Layer
zfull.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where sea

fracOutLut.comment: cumulative fractional transitions over the year; note that fraction should be reported as fraction of atmospheric grid cell
fracOutLut.long_name: annual gross fraction of land use tile  that was transferred into other land use tiles

libmassbf.comment: Specific mass balance means the net rate at which ice is added per unit area at the land ice base. Computed as the total basal mass balance on the land ice portion of the grid cell divided by land ice area in the grid cell. A negative value means loss of ice
libmassbf.long_name: Land ice basal mass balance flux
libmassbf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

lithk.comment: The thickness of the ice sheet
lithk.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

vvelbase.long_name: Y-component of land ice basal velocity
vvelbase.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

lifmassbf.comment: Total mass balance at the ice front (or vertical margin). It includes both iceberg calving and melt on vertical ice front
lifmassbf.long_name: Land ice vertical front mass balance flux
lifmassbf.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

depth.long_name: Sea Floor Depth: formula term: thetao

eta.long_name: Sea Surface Height formula term: thetao

cLitterLut.comment: end of year values (not annual mean)
cLitterLut.long_name: Carbon  in Above and Below Ground Litter Pools on Landuse Tiles

sftgif.comment: Percentage of grid cell occupied by glaciers.
sftgif.long_name: Percentage of Grid Cell Covered with Glacier
sftgif.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet

limnsw.comment: Computed as the volume times density
limnsw.long_name: Ice sheet mass that does not displace sea water
limnsw.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where grounded_ice_sheet

rsdoabsorb.long_name: Net Rate of Absorption of Shortwave Energy in Ocean Layer

opottemppadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized eddy advection (any form of eddy advection). Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.
opottemppadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized eddy advection

litempbot.comment: Basal temperature that is used to force the ice sheet models. Report temperature AT interface. Beneath ice shelves it is the temperature AT ice ocean interface. Beneath grounded ice, it is the temperature AT ice bedrock interface
litempbot.long_name: Temperature at the basal interface of the land ice.
litempbot.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where ice_sheet
